'''Lagos Television''' (abbreviated '''LTV'''), or '''Lagos Weekend Television''' (abbreviated '''LWT''', [[UHF]] channel 35, also known as '''LTV 8''')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://encomium.ng/fashola-orders-environmental-sanitation-at-ltv-8/|website=Encomium|accessdate=17 September 2014|title=Fashola orders environmental Sanitation at LTV 8}}</ref> is a [[state owned]] [[television station]] in [[Ikeja]], [[Lagos, Nigeria]]. Lagos State Television was established in October, 1980 and was the first Television station in Nigeria to operate on two frequencies / bands VHF and UHF but now on UHF channel 35 and the first state owned Television station on cable satellite [[DStv|DSTV]] channel 256 and later on [[StarTimes|Startimes]] channel 104.
